comments.body:
The benchmark (part of [my branch](https://github.com/LarryRuane/bitcoin/commits/2022-11-pr26152-refactor)) experienced a near-infinite loop without this change. The reason is that the benchmark test mempool has such a high degree of fan-out and fan-in that a single transaction could be added to the `to_process` set over and over. Of course, std::set doesn't allow duplicates, but I added some debug logging that shows the same tx being added, removed, processed, then added again, many times. This change fixed the problem completely.
```suggestion
                    if (!ancestors.count(parent_it)) {
                        to_process.insert(parent_it);
                        ancestors.insert(parent_it);
                    }
```

